version.body:
This sounds like a good idea, but should only be enabled in non-production environments. (And easily turned off or on.)
That said, this is a feature request, and would need to have a patch against Rails master to get integrated into Rails.
I'd also suggest that you get your users to +1 it here.
Assigning to DHH due to his "Rave Review" at the bottom of http://github.com/anildigital/partioprint ;)

version.body: I think it should stay as a patch. A framework should optimize because you don't know the end user's use case all the time, and if they have a lot of partals that is a lot of extra info down the wire, and exposes part of your implementation that many companies may not want to happen. I think keep it as a plugin. If you want it make it only work if you turn it on.
